# JavaScript Functions: Basics

```javascript
// Function declaration
function sum(a, b) {
    return a + b;
}

// Function call
const result = sum(5, 3);
console.log(`The sum is: ${result}`);
```

### Function Components:

| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| Declaration | Define the function with a name and parameters |
| Invocation | Execute the function code |
| Parameters | Inputs to customize function behavior |

## JavaScript Higher-Order Functions

### Example: Using `map` Function

```javascript
// Array of numbers
const numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4];

// Using map to square each number
const squares = numbers.map(function(num) {
    return num * num;
});

console.log(squares); // Output: [1, 4, 9, 16]
```

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Numbers Array] --> B{map function}
    B --> C[Square Each Number]
    C --> D[New Array of Squares]
```

### Key Characteristics:

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `map` | Transform array elements |
| `filter` | Select elements based on condition |
| `reduce` | Aggregate array elements into a single value |
